On Wed, Apr 4, 2012 at 2:00 PM, Mike Kelly &lt;mikekelly321@...&gt; wrote:

&gt; The problem with JSON-LD is that it is way too complex.
&gt;
&gt;
Voila. Moving on...



&gt; Most people are just looking for conventions for linking to
&gt; and representing containment/embeddedness of other resources, and leaving
&gt; resource state alone as plain old JSON properties.
&gt;
&gt;
See, that&#39;s exactly the point on which I realised last year that my own
reconciliation with what I thought REST was, with Linked Data, had missed
where the REST community had moved in the meantime.

I thought REST was about identifying resources and interacting with them
using a uniform interface (commonly via HTTP). In the meantime it&#39;s about
accepting that a common centralised bunch of link relations are all the
shared semantics that are needed and the rest can just be pushed into local
schemas with no sharing.

Am I being unfair?

Barry

